race.comment: CIGAR MAN (2) has hit the top-five in all six NSW starts to date and should find this assignment a touch easier. Ready to peak now at the fourth run back and gets the services of gun hoop Thompson in the irons. Should prove very hard to toss. CASTERLY ROCK (1) just ran into one better at Kilcoy over this distance range last time out and will be rock-hard fit for this. Top-three credentials. PIERTAGA (10) is a last-start winner who should be high on confidence now. Stick with her. CHAYSE 'N' PENNY (3) strips fitter third-up from the spell and cannot be left out of calculations. HIGH CLASS ROLLER (6) gets the reliable Dunn/Mallyon combination and may make his presence felt.
